Shrimp Squat Progressions
‚†Ä
This is the move I am currently mastering (form could be prettier but I‚Äôm excited about it)!
‚†Ä
This video is for you if you are experienced with lunges & pistol squats. These progressions will work for you.
‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£reverse lunges
2Ô∏è‚É£reverse lunge landing GENTLY on your knee
3Ô∏è‚É£repeat #2 on an elevated surface then go into a shrimp squat on that elevated surface
4Ô∏è‚É£ remove the elevated surface & trust yourself
‚†Ä
*alternate legs occasionally to avoid one leg burning out
*practice makes perfectüëåüèª I am still mastering my form & haven‚Äôt quite mastered 2 hands on my foot yet which is the next progression!
*warm up beforehand, it‚Äôs not unusual to get a hamstring cramp by simply getting in the position to start a shrimp squat
*have fun üòç that‚Äôs what this is all about! #shrimpsquat #fitnessisfun #dontoverthinkit

Will you gain weight if you stop weighing yourself?
‚†Ä
First let‚Äôs address the elephant in the room, yes my scale is dusty AF, no I haven‚Äôt used it in months, and YES I finally took it to the basement last night üò≠üôåüèªüôåüèª
‚†Ä
So let‚Äôs break the original question down a bit.....Just because you stop weighing yourself doesn‚Äôt mean you‚Äôre going to stop with your day to day habits so the answer is typically no.
‚†Ä
Reasons why I stopped weighing myself
‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£ I make health decisions for my greater good now, not to wake up at a lower number.
2Ô∏è‚É£ I have more mental space to think about the important things in life such as my relationships & being the best wife, family member, friend & coach I can be
3Ô∏è‚É£ My days are lead by gratitude when I wake up, not by anxiety because ‚Äúmy weight is up‚Äù
4Ô∏è‚É£ I‚Äôm more in tune with my body and my natural fullness/ hunger cues because I am not eating to be lighter.
5Ô∏è‚É£ I don‚Äôt ‚Äúneed‚Äù to be shredded, a certain # on the scale anymore. I GET to move my body & fuel it with great food to feel amazing and being athletic & fit are a byproduct üòâ
6Ô∏è‚É£ less stress & overthinking my weight = easier to maintain.
‚†Ä
I used to weigh myself multiple times a day for years just an FYI so yesterday when I brought that unused scale to the basement after months of not stepping on it, I felt like I entered a new chapter. üôåüèª
‚†Ä
I am soul in a body having a human experience. As Gabby Bernstein says, ‚ÄúThe body heals when we‚Äôre not looking at it.‚Äù
‚†Ä
Do you guys weigh yourselves?

Reasons why I run & why I recommend jogging as a recovery movement choice for my clients:
‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£It‚Äôs a form of meditation & a way for me to silence my thoughts.
2Ô∏è‚É£It‚Äôs an excuse for me to get outside & experience the healing benefits of nature.
3Ô∏è‚É£I do it for fun, not to perform a certain way, therefore there is 0 pressure. I listen to my body.. Somedays that‚Äôs just 2 miles and others it‚Äôs 4-5 miles.
4Ô∏è‚É£It‚Äôs fun to see how fast my endurance improves the more consistent I am with it.
5Ô∏è‚É£It‚Äôs EASY to do just about anywhere with no gym.
6Ô∏è‚É£It has proven time after time to keep my legs in the best shape ever (combined with resistance training & plyos)
‚†Ä
If running sounds awful to you, don‚Äôt be so quick to judge it. Approach it in a non intimidating way and start with half walks/half jogs then build yourself up to jogging an entire mile.. then 2.. then 3+. You may surprise yourself!
‚†Ä
The major key here is placing no pressure or expectations on yourself. No judgement or shame = pure enjoyment.
‚†Ä

If you squeeze an orange you will always get orange juice out of it.
‚†Ä
It doesn‚Äôt matter how you squeeze it, who squeezes it or what you squeeze it with, you will always get orange juice.. because that is what‚Äôs inside.
‚†Ä
The same logic applies to you.
‚†Ä
If someone ‚Äúsqueezes‚Äù you & puts pressure on you or says something unflattering to you & anger, shame, bitterness, depression, or anxiety comes out it‚Äôs because that‚Äôs what‚Äôs inside. (Analogy from Wayne Dyer)
‚†Ä
ü§Øü§Øü§Ø ok. Lol. This is a concept I was well aware of but Wayne Dyer‚Äôs usage of the orange analogy really made it click.
‚†Ä
& to top it allllllll off you cannot give away what you don‚Äôt have. So if you don‚Äôt have happiness or love in your heart, you cannot give it away.
‚†Ä
For those of you that think self-care or working on yourself is selfish- I hope this made a few things ‚Äúclick‚Äù for you. What a refreshing reminder.

‚úÖ1/4 almond meal
‚úÖ1 scoop level 1 protein powder (vanilla or ice cream sandwich preferably)
‚úÖ 1 cup peanut butter
‚úÖ1/4 cup honey

‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£mix almond meal & protein powder in medium mixing bowl
2Ô∏è‚É£put honey & peanut butter in smaller mixing bowl and melt together in microwave (about 20-30 seconds)
3Ô∏è‚É£pour honey/pb mixture into dry ingredients
4Ô∏è‚É£pour mixture into an 8x8 pan that is lined with parchment paper
5Ô∏è‚É£freeze for 10-15 minutes or until firm
6Ô∏è‚É£ cut into 12 squares and put melted chocolate on top.
7Ô∏è‚É£store in fridge ü§©

Can you lose weight & intuitively eat?
‚†Ä
So you‚Äôve been dieting for a long time & you fear that if you step away from dieting or tracking your macros or calories that you will rapidly gain weight.
‚†Ä
Intuitive or mindful eating doesn‚Äôt mean loss of control. Here‚Äôs what the transition could look like for you & what I take my clients through‚§µÔ∏è
‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a meal plan every few weeks with your favorite staples with balanced meals (protein, carbs, fat, fiber) that make you feel good & loosely follow that for a while.
2Ô∏è‚É£ Start paying attention to how certain foods make you feel.
3Ô∏è‚É£ Start noticing hunger & fullness cues. are you extremely hungry after breakfast? What does this mean? Was it what you ate or do you need more food? What does being full (not stuffed) feel like? Notice that feeling (close your eyes and visualize what it feels like) & next time it will be easier to stop when you‚Äôre full bc you know what that feeling feels like.
‚†Ä
Here‚Äôs HOW & WHY you can lose weight eating like this
‚†Ä
‚úÖYou will be more connected to your fullness cues therefore you‚Äôll understand how to stop when you‚Äôre full on an everyday basis (no more binging/overeating).
‚úÖYou will kick the guilt & shame when it comes dieting because you have learned to honor your bodies needs & you are focusing on foods that make you FEEL good. Food is neutral, some just make you feel better than others. (aka no more binge/restrict which equals consistency & we all know consistency = results).
‚úÖIt teaches you how to eat for life. There‚Äôs always going to be vacations, dinner parties, etc. to attend. When you honor your bodies needs you won‚Äôt feel a need to overindulge during outings like these.
‚†Ä
Hope this makes sense! If you have any questions just comment below üòÅ #intuitiveeating #mindfuleating

How to achieve food freedom
‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£Work on inner peace through mindfulness practices
‚†Ä
Strengthening our mindfulness muscle through practices such as journaling, meditation, walking outdoors, etc. allows us to be more mindful in everyday situations such as stopping to think ‚Äúdo I really want this food or is there an underlying emotional reason that I am not addressing‚Äù instead of going on autopilot to the pantry.
‚†Ä
2Ô∏è‚É£Stop restricting yourself
‚†Ä
Its just like when your mom told you you couldn‚Äôt have something when you were little, it made you want it that much more. If you release any crazy ‚Äúrules‚Äù you have around food, you will not feel tempted to break them. You will be empowered to make your own decisions for your greater good.
‚†Ä
3Ô∏è‚É£Learn to trust your intuition by not relying on macros anymore
‚†Ä
This ties into number 2 ALSO sometimes when we track macros we become so obsessed with how many carbs/fat/proteins are in each item that we aren‚Äôt even aware of how bloated or crappy certain foods are making us feel.
‚†Ä
4Ô∏è‚É£Be patient & handle yourself with grace
‚†Ä
This is the most important one. Achieving food freedom takes time and effort. Just like learning to ride a bike takes time. You try, you fall down, you try, you fall down, you try & you finally learn how to ride a bike AND even after you learn how to ride a bike you may fall a few times. Handling yourself with compassion & grace is key. You cannot guilt or shame yourself into doing the best thing for yourself. Celebrate the small wins- you CAN love yourself into doing the right thing for yourself. #foodfreedom #mindfuleating

Everything is not as it seems..
‚†Ä
You see, I‚Äôve done the whole ‚Äútake fitness to extremes‚Äù thing (for 7 years to be exact).
‚†Ä
I pushed, pushed, pushed and although I am proud of what I was able to achieve, I very much lost myself in the process.
‚†Ä
I achieved pro status & was a top national level competitor for years, got shredded whenever I wanted, appeared in multiple fitness magazines across the nation on multiple occasions (like the picture on the left), in multiple ads across the world, got multiple paid sponsorship deals, and built a business out of competing.
‚†Ä
What you didn‚Äôt see were the times that sucked... such as binge eating, rapid weight gain if I wasn‚Äôt preparing for a show or shoot, depression, poor quality of life, isolation, so entirely disconnected to myself, and poor relationships.
‚†Ä
The fitness industry is an incredible place however it is my responsibility to speak out and make sure I am helping those who were once in my shoes..
‚†Ä
‚úÖYou 100% CAN achieve results without going to extremes.
‚úÖ None of the ‚Äúsuccess‚Äù is worth it if you are not happy inside & don‚Äôt love who you are.
‚úÖ If you don‚Äôt love the process, you won‚Äôt sustain the results.
‚úÖ You can build a lifestyle that still incorporates everything you love about fitness but allows for BALANCE.
‚úÖYou can still maintain a beautiful, athletic, and feminine shape without going to extremes or being shredded.
‚úÖ Beware of shiny object syndrome- shredded bodies are fun to look at on the internet but ask yourself what kind of lifestyle would that entail for me?
‚úÖ If I created a new lifestyle that I love (right pic) that doesn‚Äôt revolve around when my next meal is/constant workouts AND I am able to maintain a strong athletic physique & mind.. SO. CAN. YOU. #happinessequalsuccess

The only thing worse than being stuck in the yo-yo dieting cycle & constant shame is not thinking there is a way out of it.
‚†Ä
FYI: there is 100% a way out. I am proof. If I did it, so can you. I promise.
‚†Ä
You guys, yo-yo dieting & constant shame was my life from 2014-2017 (left picture is from 2017 when I had gained 10 lbs after vacation aka a common non competition photo that nobody ever saw). Competing at such a high level definitely got the best of me.
‚†Ä
I gained weight after every vacation. I punished myself with hours of cardio. I ate less than 1000 calories a day during the week only to go wild on the weekends. I was obsessed with food & exercising- it‚Äôs all I thought about. I literally dreamed about food, I overate any chance I could get. I thought about my next ‚Äúcheat meal‚Äù every Monday. I dug myself in the deepest mental holes every Monday & punished myself with cardio, fasting, and sauna and called it ‚Äúdamage control.‚Äù
‚†Ä
Before this shit gets too dark..... THERE IS A WAY OUT I PROMISE YOU!
‚†Ä
Here are some things my clients see when they start working with me:
‚†Ä
üôåüèª less food focused
üôåüèª listening to their bodies more & not relying on a meal plan 24/7
üôåüèª maintaining or losing weight on WAY LESS exercise
üôåüèªlearning they are worthy of their goals therefore the goals happen & are sustained!
üôåüèª coming back from vacation with no weight gain besides MAYBE water weight
üôåüèªtrust in their ability to eat mindfully & also indulge in moderation
‚†Ä
The right picture is now! & I experience all of these as well! When you join us over here at Katie Miller Fitness LLC, your life will be changed.. forever. üíó
‚†Ä

BASE:
‚†Ä
2 large sweet potatoes
1/2 cup almond milk
1 vanilla bean
1 tablespoon coconut oil
2/4 teaspoons cinnamon
2/4 teaspoons salt
1/4 teaspoon nutmeg
1/8 teaspoon white pepper
‚†Ä
TOPPING:
‚†Ä
1/2 cup oats
1/2 cup pecans
I/4 cup almond meal
I/8 teaspoon cinnamon

‚†Ä

1Ô∏è‚É£Preheat oven to 375 degrees & grease a square pyrex
2Ô∏è‚É£Prick sweet potatoes all over with fork & bake for approximately 1 hour or until soft. Let potatoes cool, then peel skin off with hands (should come  right off). Chop peeled potatoes into large chunks and transfer into a mixing bowl
3Ô∏è‚É£While potatoes bake pour almond milk into a saucepan. Split vanilla bean and scrap seeds out. Pour vanilla bean & pod into then saucepan with the almond milk & heat (without boiling) for ~5 min. Remove from heat & let steep.
4Ô∏è‚É£Remove pod & pour mixture into the sweet potato chunks, add coconut oil, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, white pepper.
5Ô∏è‚É£Mash potatoes together (taste and add additional spices if you want. Could even add dried cranberries for additional sweetness) & transfer to square Pyrex
6Ô∏è‚É£Mix all ingredients for the topping in a separate bowl then sprinkle on top of the potatoes
7Ô∏è‚É£Bake until topping is toasted for about 25 minutes. Serve warm
